<plot>A true and equal friendship between a blind young man, Barak, and a sighted girl, Orna, is interpreted by a journalist as an act of altruistic devotion. Orna is interviewed on television and collaborates with her interviewers, who glorify her for her deeds and reinforce the wrong stereotypes about people who are deprived of sight.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?226567</url></doc>
